default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default2.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere is a lack of clarity about how government has chosen its priority areas
default, and in particular how LCICG has chosen 
defaulttarget technology areas
default. 
default&#xa0;
default2.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultParticularly striking is the absence of both aviation and automotive technologies 
defaultfrom the LCICG list of target technologies 
default(with the exception of hydrogen, for which a TINA is yet to be 
defaultreleased). Aviation and automotive sectors both receive innovation support from government, and have well-developed industrial strategies. Recent evidence presented to UCL’s Green Economy Policy Commission
default (to be published in early 2014)
default also suggests that
default the UK has a weaker performance in low-carbon innovation in these two sectors (as measured by patents), than other major economies. Furthermore, the Committee on Climate Change
default highlighted both aviation and electric vehicle technologies as priority techn
defaultology areas. 
