default2.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMoreover
default, low-carbon innovation should not only address energy technologies. A
default broader low-carbon perspective might include agricultural technologies and techniques, and land-u
defaultse management, for example. 
defaultSimilarly, it might move beyond techn
defaultologies to support low-carbon 
defaultbusiness models. 
defaultKey carbon-intensive sectors may be better ways of structuring government strategy around low carbon innovation needs
default and opportunities. 
default&#xa0;
default2.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe TINA process has been valuable in highlighting the innovation pote
defaultntial of a small number of key technologies
default and technology areas
default.
default It is to be hoped that the process can expand its view of technology areas of relevance, including those that are less well represented in systems modelling tools (either because they are le
defaultss mature, or because there is disagreement about technology cost estimates). Potentially important options excluded from the current set of TINAS include some that are technically achievable, but which would raise significant governance challenges (e.g. H
default2
default in gas networks), and those that are longer term and more speculative (tethered high-altitude wind turbines; direct photocatalysis; various energy harvesting technologies). 
